    <!-- Guide Detail -->
    <string name="guide.prepareForSurvey.introduction">Introduction:</string>
    <string name="guide.prepareForSurvey.introductionParagraph">As an observer on a vessel, you are looking for debris that is floating in the sea and recording it while sighted.</string>
    <string name="guide.prepareForSurvey.Observer">Observer:</string>
    <string name="guide.prepareForSurvey.observerParagraph">Each survey will take 1 hour, which requires full attention and sufficient batttery of your device. As an observer it is important to choose the best side of the vessel related to sunlight and wind conditions. The observer's standing point must remain the same during the entire 1 hour visual survey.</string>

    <string name="guide.startingASurvey.introduction">Introduction:</string>
    <string name="guide.startingASurvey.introductionParagraph">To start a new visual survey, you can navigate back to the 'Welcome' page of the Ocean Cleanup Visual Survey App. Choose 'Start a new survey' to start with the 1-hour sighting. </string>
    <string name="guide.startingASurvey.observer">Observer:</string>
    <string name="guide.startingASurvey.observerParagraph">Before you start a new survey, it is important that you have filled in your personal and vessel details. This enables us to link the survey-data to the right vessel and team.</string>

    <string name="guide.enterAnSpotter.info">Info:</string>
    <string name="guide.enterAnSpotter.infoParagraph">To setup your observer profile, you can navigate back to the 'Welcome' page of the Ocean Cleanup Visual Survey App. Choose 'Ready to get started' to fill in your personal and vessel details. We will ask you to fill in the name of the oberserver, the data recorder, the platform height and the name of your vessel. You will be able to update or delete this information when necessary.</string>

    <string name="guide.howToReportFeedback.title">Got Feedback?</string>
    <string name="guide.howToReportFeedback.paragraph">Is the answer to your question not available in this guide? Do you experience a problem with the use of the app or when conducting a survey? Please don't hesitate to contact us.</string>
